      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then were they all of good cheer.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The words present a striking contrast to the despair of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 27:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The hearty cheerfulness (is it too colloquial a phrase to say the “pluck”?) of the Apostle had communicated itself, as by a kind of electric sympathy, to his companions. They looked to him as their friend and leader, and had spirits to eat once more.",
        "children": []
      },
